s:31:\"Mon, 08 Feb 2021 11:00:12 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"language\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"en-US\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"generator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://wordpress.org/?v=5.7-beta2-50282\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"item\";a:10:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"Themes Team Meeting Agenda for February 09, 2021\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:93:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/08/themes-team-meeting-agenda-for-february-09-2021/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/08/themes-team-meeting-agenda-for-february-09-2021/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 08 Feb 2021 11:00:12 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Uncategorized\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/?p=20121\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:380:\"The themes team conducts a meeting on the second and fourth Tuesday of the month. Along with the fixed agendas, we have an open floor at the end where you can ask or share anything related to themes. We encourage all members and anyone interested to attend. Channel: #themereview &#124; Time: Tuesday, February 09 2021, 15:00 UTC Meeting agenda Weekly updates Get [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"kafleg\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2385:\"<p id=\"block-a384c334-61e8-42f9-9fe8-9b33e91e3db0\">The themes team conducts a meeting on the <strong>second</strong> and <strong>fourth</strong> Tuesday of the month.</p>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"block-f6c3d0aa-da6d-4a76-9e50-d3535d7e2cf7\">Along with the fixed agendas, we have an open floor at the end where you can ask or share anything related to themes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p id=\"block-5442b1bd-01b0-47f2-b4e5-24038320a7f0\">We encourage all members and anyone interested to attend.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Channel: <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://wordpress.slack.com/messages/themereview/\" target=\"_blank\">#themereview</a> | Time: <strong><a href=\"https://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?iso=20210209T1500\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Tuesday, February 09 2021, 15:00 UTC</a></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Meeting agenda</h2>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Weekly updates</li><li>Get work update about the theme unit test </li><li>Open Floor</li></ol><h3>Weekly Updates</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Current statistics can be found on: <a href=\"https://themes.trac.wordpress.org/\">https://themes.trac.wordpress.org/</a> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Themes Trac ticket graph: <a href=\"https://themes.trac.wordpress.org/ticketgraph\">https://themes.trac.wordpress.org/ticketgraph</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check regular weekly updates <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/updates/tag/themes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Theme Unit Test Work Update </h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/technocrews/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>technocrews</a> is taking this responsibility along with <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/mahesh901122/\">@mahesh901122</a>, <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/musamamasood/\">@musamamasood</a> for updating the theme unit test. Here is the current status of the theme unit test in <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://github.com/WPTT/theme-unit-test\" target=\"_blank\">GitHub</a>.  If you want to contribute, you can directly start from GitHub or contact <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/williampatton/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>williampatton</a> for any help.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Open Floor</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We will discuss everything related to themes. Attendees can ask or share themes related things.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please comment in the comment box below if you have anything to bring up during the open floor.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/08/themes-team-meeting-agenda-for-february-09-2021/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:30:\"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1\";a:1:{s:7:\"post-id\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"20121\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"Gutenberg + Themes: Week of Feb 1, 2021\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/05/gutenberg-themes-week-of-feb-1-2021/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/05/gutenberg-themes-week-of-feb-1-2021/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 05 Feb 2021 15:31:22 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Uncategorized\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"gutenberg-themes-roundup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/?p=20115\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:369:\"Hello! This is the 37th weekly roundup of theme-related discussions, fixes, and developments in Gutenberg.  Please weigh in on the tickets below — your voice and feedback are welcome!  Issues / Discussions &#38; PRs: FSE Blocks: Enabling FSE blocks in classic themes 28744 Global Styles: Discuss the default scope of each block’s style properties: 27512 [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Jeff Ong\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4832:\"<p>Hello! This is the 37th weekly roundup of theme-related discussions, fixes, and developments in Gutenberg. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please weigh in on the tickets below — your voice and feedback are welcome! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Issues / Discussions &amp; PRs:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>FSE Blocks: Enabling FSE blocks in classic themes <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28744\">28744</a></li><li>Global Styles: Discuss the default scope of each block’s style properties: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/27512\">27512</a></li><li>FSE: Improve loading method for block styles in FSE themes <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28358\">28358</a></li><li>FSE: Load page templates via theme.json <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28700\">28700</a></li><li>FSE Blocks: Navigation block: Hide more than N items. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/27131\">27131</a></li><li>FSE: Hide Homepage title <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28564\">28564</a></li><li>FSE Blocks: Query Block: Consider allowing for an optional semantic wrapper tag <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28555\">28555</a></li><li>FSE: Add a ‘section’ term for Template Parts. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28410\">28410</a></li><li>FSE: Change the post template visually <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28390\">28390</a></li><li>FSE: Site Editing: Explore how we might set what’s displayed on the front of a site from within the site editor <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28341\">28341</a></li><li>Buttons block radius and outline size change <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28514\">28514</a></li><li>Dropcap behavior <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28685\">28685</a></li></ul><p>Merged/fixed:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>FSE: Allow the query block to work on singular pages when inheriting the global query <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28351\">28351</a></li><li>Global Styles: Make custom spacing work with core <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28548\">28548</a></li><li>Global Styles: Update theme.json shape: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28533\">28533</a></li><li>Global Styles: add support for border config via theme.json <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28049\">28049</a></li><li>Menu item word wrap: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28516\">28516</a></li><li>Image border radius support: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27667\">27667</a></li><li>Social Icons, background and color options: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28084\">28084</a></li><li>Cover: remove 100% height <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28455\">28455</a></li></ul><p>Overview Issues:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Full Site Editing Milestones. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24551\">24551</a></li><li>Template Tags in Full Site Editing. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/22724\">22724</a> </li><li>Missing query block functionality. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24934\">24934</a></li><li>Query and Loop block tracking: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24762\">24762</a></li></ul><p>General Resources:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/labels/%5BFeature%5D%20Full%20Site%20Editing\">GitHub Issues: Full Site Editing</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/labels/%5BFeature%5D%20Themes\">GitHub  Issues: Themes</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/blob/master/docs/designers-developers/developers/themes/block-based-themes.md\">Block-based Themes Reference</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/tutorials/block-based-themes/\">Block-based Themes Tutorial</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/developers/themes/theme-json/\">Experimental-Themes.json</a></li><li><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/07/05/using-the-block-editor-for-theme-parts/\">Using the Block Editor for Theme Parts</a></li><li><a href=\"https://wp.me/p29gdg-4MC\">Printing navigation-block HTML from a legacy menu in themes</a></li></ul><p>Thanks to <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kjellr/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>kjellr</a>, <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/scruffian/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>scruffian</a>, and Joen for help pulling this post together. Please let us know if it was helpful in the comments!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/tags/gutenberg-themes-roundup/\" class=\"tag\"><span class=\"tag-prefix\">#</span>gutenberg-themes-roundup</a></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/05/gutenberg-themes-week-of-feb-1-2021/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:30:\"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1\";a:1:{s:7:\"post-id\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"20115\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"Gutenberg 9.9: New JSON structure for theme.json files\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/04/gutenberg-9-9-new-json-structure-for-theme-json-files/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:108:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/04/gutenberg-9-9-new-json-structure-for-theme-json-files/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 04 Feb 2021 11:04:01 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Uncategorized\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/?p=20107\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:330:\"Gutenberg 9.9 changes the structure of theme.json files for experimental Full Site Editing (FSE) themes. The changes made are a first step to allowing theme metadata and more granular control for FSE in the future. More details on that process and what to expect in the future can be found in the Overview GitHub ticket. [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Ari Stathopoulos\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1898:\"<p>Gutenberg 9.9 changes the structure of <code>theme.json</code> files for experimental Full Site Editing (FSE) themes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The changes made are a first step to allowing theme metadata and more granular control for FSE in the future. More details on that process and what to expect in the future can be found in the <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28163\">Overview GitHub ticket</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/developers/themes/theme-json/\">Documentation for <code>theme.json</code></a> has been updated and is properly maintained so theme developers experimenting with FSE can follow that and update their files accordingly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The structural changes that went in Gutenberg 9.9 can be found in <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28110\">Pull Request #28110 in the Gutenberg project</a> and can be summed-up in the following:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><code>settings</code> and <code>styles</code> and now on the root level of the JSON file</li><li><code>global</code> was renamed to <code>root</code></li></ul><p>With <code>settings</code> and <code>styles</code> in the root level it is now easier to group all block settings in one place and all block styles in a separate area, therefore making it easier to navigate the file and get an overview, while at the same time making it easier to extend the file’s functionality in the future.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before:</p>\n\n\n<pre class=\"brush: jscript; title: ; notranslate\">\n{\n  \"global\": {\n    \"settings\": { ... },\n    \"styles\": { ... }\n  },\n  \"core/paragraph\": {\n    \"settings\": { ... },\n    \"styles\": { ... }\n  }\n}\n</pre>\n\n\n<p>After:</p>\n\n\n<pre class=\"brush: jscript; title: ; notranslate\">\n{\n  \"settings\": {\n    \"defaults\": { ... },\n    \"root\": { ... },\n    \"core/paragraph\": { ... }\n  },\n  \"styles\": {\n    \"root\": { ... },\n    \"core/paragraph\": { ... }\n  }\n}\n\n</pre>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/04/gutenberg-9-9-new-json-structure-for-theme-json-files/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:30:\"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1\";a:1:{s:7:\"post-id\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"20107\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"Block-based Meeting Notes – February 3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/03/block-based-meeting-notes-february-3/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/03/block-based-meeting-notes-february-3/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 03 Feb 2021 18:24:02 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Uncategorized\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"block-based-meeting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Meeting Notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/?p=20099\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:406:\"First, thank you all for your active participation in this meeting. The meeting was held based on this meeting agenda. Channel: #themereviewFacilitated by @kjellr Notes Taken: @ashiquzzaman Block-based Theme Updates in Gutenberg Gutenberg 9.9 is coming out on Friday! This includes new formatting rules for experimental-theme.json, so if you haven’t updated your block-based themes yet, please [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Kjell Reigstad\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9035:\"<p>First, thank you all for your active participation in this meeting. The meeting was held based on this <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/02/block-based-themes-meeting-agenda-feb-3-2021/\">meeting agenda</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Channel: <a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/tags/themereview/\">#themereview</a><br>Facilitated by <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kjellr/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>kjellr</a> <br>Notes Taken: <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/ashiquzzaman/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>ashiquzzaman</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2><strong>Block-based Theme Updates in Gutenberg</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Gutenberg 9.9 is coming out on Friday! This includes new formatting rules for experimental-theme.json, so if you haven’t updated your block-based themes yet, please <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/developers/themes/theme-json/\">take a look at the docs</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Couple of PRs that need highlight:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>A new Post Navigation block is in the works here and could use some testing: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28602\">https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28602</a></li><li><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/aristath/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>aristath</a> is working on a cool PR that would improve front-end performance for FSE themes: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28358\">https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28358</a></li></ul><p>Please give those a test if you have a moment!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>TT1 Blocks Updates</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>TT1 Blocks’ experimental-theme.json file has been updated to work with the upcoming Gutenberg v9.9 release: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/theme-experiments/pull/182\">https://github.com/WordPress/theme-experiments/pull/182</a> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>At the moment, that’s only available in the version from the GitHub repo, not <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/themes/tt1-blocks/\">the version in the theme repository</a>. <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kjellr/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>kjellr</a> will submit the update to the Theme Repository shortly after the Gutenberg plugin update is live to minimize any compatibility hiccups.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just a couple other updates:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/poena/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>poena</a> has been keeping up this helpful checklist of theme updates to make it compatible with the upcoming WordPress 5.7 release: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/theme-experiments/issues/181\">https://github.com/WordPress/theme-experiments/issues/181</a></li><li><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/scruffian/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>scruffian</a> pulled together a list of all the template tags used in Twenty Twenty-One to help analyze what features are still missing: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/22724#issuecomment-771788465\">https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/22724#issuecomment-771788465</a></li></ul><p>For the status of everything else, check out the TT1 Blocks project board: <br><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/theme-experiments/projects/1\">https://github.com/WordPress/theme-experiments/projects/1</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Discussion Topic: How might classic themes migrate to block-based themes?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Background:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24313\">General idea + discussion</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24834\">Falling back to PHP templates when no block-based templates are present</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24803\">PHP Theme template conversions</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/25316\">A prototype for allowing PHP in block templates</a></li></ul><p><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/pbking/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>pbking</a> asked – Are there plans to make dynamic blocks available to PHP templates? Allow for the transition to start using some of them instead of calls to PHP functions without going all-in. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Example: https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/22724#issuecomment-771788465</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kjellr/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>kjellr</a> replied with – There have been discussions about that sort of thing <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/21932\">here</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/20966\">here</a>. In general though, it seemed to me that folks were leaning more towards having a pretty limited set of PHP functions available. And then scaling up from there as needed, versus opening the door to all of the standard PHP functions available.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/aristath/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>aristath</a>’s explorations here might be of interest:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-wp-embed is-provider-make-wordpress-themes wp-block-embed-make-wordpress-themes\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"6iF36nEWry\"><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/07/05/using-the-block-editor-for-theme-parts/\">Using the block editor for theme-parts</a></blockquote><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"“Using the block editor for theme-parts” — Make WordPress Themes\" src=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/07/05/using-the-block-editor-for-theme-parts/embed/#?secret=6iF36nEWry\" data-secret=\"6iF36nEWry\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe>\n</div></figure><figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-wp-embed is-provider-make-wordpress-themes wp-block-embed-make-wordpress-themes\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"UlpKDa3iBt\"><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/07/06/printing-navigation-block-html-from-a-legacy-menu-in-themes/\">Printing navigation-block HTML from a legacy menu in themes</a></blockquote><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"“Printing navigation-block HTML from a legacy menu in themes” — Make WordPress Themes\" src=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/07/06/printing-navigation-block-html-from-a-legacy-menu-in-themes/embed/#?secret=UlpKDa3iBt\" data-secret=\"UlpKDa3iBt\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe>\n</div></figure><p><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/pbking/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>pbking</a> – There aren’t blocks that are only available in Block-based FSE themes? </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kjellr/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>kjellr</a> –  There are, but Gutenberg should probably allow for those to be present in special cases when FSE isn’t active.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/poena/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>poena</a> – “<a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24834\">Falling back to PHP templates when no block-based templates are present</a>” seems doable but if the reason for doing it, is that we can not do what we want in an FSE theme, this is the wrong way to solve that. I think that makes sense just in the context of gradually “upgrading” to FSE: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24803\">https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24803</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/poena/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>poena</a> – We should allow for global styles for old themes without the site editor.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Open Floor</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/poena/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>poena</a> – There are themes being submitted to the <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/theme-experiments/\">https://github.com/WordPress/theme-experiments/</a> repo but nobody is reviewing them, help is needed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/pbking/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>pbking</a> and <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/scruffian/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>scruffian</a> offered to help review. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Any comments and discussion can be done via the below comment box.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/tags/block-based-meeting/\" class=\"tag\"><span class=\"tag-prefix\">#</span>block-based-meeting</a>, #meeting-notes</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/03/block-based-meeting-notes-february-3/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:30:\"com-wordpress:feed-additions:1\";a:1:{s:7:\"post-id\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"20099\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"Gutenberg + Themes: Week of Jan 25, 2021\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/03/gutenberg-themes-week-of-jan-25-2021/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/03/gutenberg-themes-week-of-jan-25-2021/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 03 Feb 2021 15:48:52 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Uncategorized\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"gutenberg-themes-roundup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/?p=20096\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:367:\"Hello! This is the 36th weekly roundup of theme-related discussions, fixes, and developments in Gutenberg. Sorry it’s late! Please weigh in on the tickets below — your voice and feedback are welcome!  Issues / Discussions: Blocks: Refactor Gallery Block as a wrapper around Image Blocks. 25940 Global Styles: Discuss the default scope of each block’s [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"scruffian\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5850:\"<p>Hello! This is the 36th weekly roundup of theme-related discussions, fixes, and developments in Gutenberg. Sorry it’s late!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please weigh in on the tickets below — your voice and feedback are welcome! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Issues / Discussions:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Blocks: Refactor Gallery Block as a wrapper around Image Blocks. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/25940\">25940</a></li><li>Global Styles: Discuss the default scope of each block’s style properties: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/27512\">27512</a></li><li>FSE: Improve loading methods for block styles. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28358\">28358</a></li><li>FSE: Updates to theme.json. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28163\">28163</a></li><li>FSE: Try implementing a multi-theme system. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28131\">28131</a></li><li>FSE: Themes located in a subdirectory do not load template parts. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28022\">28022</a></li><li>FSE Blocks: Add Archive Title Block. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27989\">27989</a></li><li>FSE Blocks: Navigation block: Hide more than N items. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/27131\">27131</a></li><li>FSE: Hide Homepage title <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28564\">28564</a></li><li>FSE Blocks: Query Block: Consider allowing for an optional semantic wrapper tag <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28555\">28555</a></li><li>Global Styles: Make custom spacing work with core <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28548\">28548</a></li><li>FSE: Improve loading method for block styles in FSE themes <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28358\">28358</a></li><li>Updates to experimental-theme.json <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28163\">28163</a></li><li>FSE: Enable the user to switch which entity is being previewed in the template editor <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28466\">28466</a></li><li>FSE: Add a ‘section’ term for Template Parts. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28410\">28410</a></li><li>FSE: Change the post template visually <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28390\">28390</a></li><li>FSE: Improve loading method for block styles in FSE themes <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28358\">28358</a></li><li>FSE: Allow the query block to work on singular pages when inheriting the global query <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28351\">28351</a></li><li>FSE: Site Editing: Explore how we might set what’s displayed on the front of a site from within the site editor <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/28341\">28341</a></li></ul><p>Merged/fixed:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>FSE: Dark Theme Support: Allow for theme modifications <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28233\">28233</a></li><li>Blocks: Fix cover matrix alignment <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28404\">28404</a></li><li>Blocks: Add support for border configuration via theme.json. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28049\">28049</a></li><li>Global Styles: Update theme.json shape: make settings &amp; style top-level keys <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28110\">28110</a></li><li>Blocks: Social Link: Add a class to the anchor element <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28494\">28494</a></li></ul><p>Overview Issues:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Full Site Editing Milestones. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24551\">24551</a></li><li>Template Tags in Full Site Editing. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/22724\">22724</a> </li><li>Missing query block functionality. <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24934\">24934</a></li><li>Query and Loop block tracking: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/issues/24762\">24762</a></li><li>Menu item word wrap: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28516\">28516</a></li><li>Image border radius support: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/27667\">27667</a></li><li>Social Icons, background and color options: <a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/pull/28084\">28084</a></li></ul><p>General Resources:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/labels/%5BFeature%5D%20Full%20Site%20Editing\">GitHub Issues: Full Site Editing</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/labels/%5BFeature%5D%20Themes\">GitHub  Issues: Themes</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/WordPress/gutenberg/blob/master/docs/designers-developers/developers/themes/block-based-themes.md\">Block-based Themes Reference</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/tutorials/block-based-themes/\">Block-based Themes Tutorial</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/block-editor/developers/themes/theme-json/\">Experimental-Themes.json</a></li><li><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2020/07/05/using-the-block-editor-for-theme-parts/\">Using the Block Editor for Theme Parts</a></li><li><a href=\"https://wp.me/p29gdg-4MC\">Printing navigation-block HTML from a legacy menu in themes</a></li></ul><p>Thanks to <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kjellr/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>kjellr</a> and <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/joen/\" class=\"mention\"><span class=\"mentions-prefix\">@</span>joen</a> for help pulling this post together. Please let us know if it was helpful in the comments!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/tags/gutenberg-themes-roundup/\" class=\"tag\"><span class=\"tag-prefix\">#</span>gutenberg-themes-roundup</a></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"https://make.wordpress.org/themes/2021/02/03/gutenberg-themes-week-of-jan-25-2021/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8: